html.body: APOPTOSIS_ENTRY module This module describes the regulation network around p53 activity. Upon DNA damage, stress-related signals or oncogenic stimulus, this pathway is activated. E2F1 induces the transcription of components of the apoptosis pathway such as p53 and p14ARF. When p53 level is high, mediated by p14ARF, the cell cycle arrests and waits for DNA to be repaired. If the repair takes too long, apoptosis is activated.
